This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a 4D reconstruction approach to crop monitoring using image sensors. The paper also addresses the problem of data association, which is a common challenge in computer vision. Additionally, the paper is relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it discusses autonomous crop monitoring, which is a task that can be performed by robots. The paper also mentions the use of precision agriculture, which involves the use of technology to optimize crop production, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the reconstruction of 3D structures, which is relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
